Text.SourceString: You and Mom looked great yesterday... You two seemed happy.//<portrait=happy>It made me happy!
Text.LocalizedString: You and Mom looked great yesterday... You two seemed happy.//<portrait=happy>It made me happy!

Text.SourceString: Dad and Aunt <NpcName>Alice</> had tears in their eyes yesterday.//<portrait=doubt>When I asked, Dad said they were happy tears...
Text.LocalizedString: Dad and Aunt <NpcName>Alice</> had tears in their eyes yesterday.//<portrait=doubt>When I asked, Dad said they were happy tears...

Text.SourceString: I miss <NpcName>Eva</>.//<portrait=happy>I'm going to see her tomorrow and make her bake me some pumpkin pies.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss <NpcName>Eva</>.//<portrait=happy>I'm going to see her tomorrow and make her bake me some pumpkin pies.

Text.SourceString: Aunt <NpcName>Alice</> said hi.
Text.LocalizedString: Aunt <NpcName>Alice</> said hi.

Text.SourceString: School is so close to our farm now! It's not like the far, far away inn...bleh!//<portrait=normal>Now I can sleep more before school.
Text.LocalizedString: School is so close to our farm now! It's not like the far, far away inn...bleh!//<portrait=normal>Now I can sleep more before school.

Text.SourceString: I had a scary dream last night, a ghost was outside taking our food...
Text.LocalizedString: I had a scary dream last night, a ghost was outside taking our food...

Text.SourceString: Do you have ghosts here? I'm telling Mom.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have ghosts here? I'm telling Mom.

Text.SourceString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I'm up early here. It's kinda fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I'm up early here. It's kinda fun.

Text.SourceString: Our house is so big, it's like a playground.//I love racing around!
Text.LocalizedString: Our house is so big, it's like a playground.//I love racing around!

Text.SourceString: I wish I could sprint around the farm, but Mom told me I need to stretch first...stretching is so boring.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could sprint around the farm, but Mom told me I need to stretch first...stretching is so boring.

Text.SourceString: I woke up to a bird singing by my window. Living on a farm is super cool!
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up to a bird singing by my window. Living on a farm is super cool!

Text.SourceString: I have to go to the inn, Dad misses me.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to go to the inn, Dad misses me.

Text.SourceString: Do we have any stuff I could give to my uncles?//<portrait=doubt>I wanna, um, surprise them with something, but I don't know what.
Text.LocalizedString: Do we have any stuff I could give to my uncles?//<portrait=doubt>I wanna, um, surprise them with something, but I don't know what.

Text.SourceString: Winter on the farm is super cool. We have snow everywhere!
Text.LocalizedString: Winter on the farm is super cool. We have snow everywhere!

Text.SourceString: Summer at the farm is super cool.//We get to plant sooo many things...it's way more fun than being at the inn, I promise.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer at the farm is super cool.//We get to plant sooo many things...it's way more fun than being at the inn, I promise.

Text.SourceString: Our farm is like Nana's garden, only it's super-duper <Italic>bigger</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Our farm is like Nana's garden, only it's super-duper <Italic>bigger</>.

Text.SourceString: Nana said I could cook curry if I had a coconut. Is that true? Do we have a coconut, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Nana said I could cook curry if I had a coconut. Is that true? Do we have a coconut, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow's the Animal Festival!//I'm going really early! I wanna see all the cute animals.
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow's the Animal Festival!//I'm going really early! I wanna see all the cute animals.

Text.SourceString: Are you and Mom going to <NpcName>Bree</>'s New Year's festival tomorrow?//It's super late, I don't think I can stay up that late.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you and Mom going to <NpcName>Bree</>'s New Year's festival tomorrow?//It's super late, I don't think I can stay up that late.

Text.SourceString: Yippie, tomorrow is Summer! I can't wait!
Text.LocalizedString: Yippie, tomorrow is Summer! I can't wait!

Text.SourceString: IT'S SNOWING, IT'S SNOWING!
Text.LocalizedString: IT'S SNOWING, IT'S SNOWING!

Text.SourceString: MOM, IT'S RAINING OUTSIDE!
Text.LocalizedString: MOM, IT'S RAINING OUTSIDE!

Text.SourceString: MOM, IT'S STORMING OUTSIDE!
Text.LocalizedString: MOM, IT'S STORMING OUTSIDE!

Text.SourceString: Oh no, I lost my fairy pen. Is it in your room, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I was playing hide and seek there yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no, I lost my fairy pen. Is it in your room, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I was playing hide and seek there yesterday.

Text.SourceString: I want curry for dinner. I'm gonna tell Mom.
Text.LocalizedString: I want curry for dinner. I'm gonna tell Mom.

Text.SourceString: Mom seems happy lately.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom seems happy lately.

Text.SourceString: I made my bed this morning! It's super neat.//Are you proud of me?
Text.LocalizedString: I made my bed this morning! It's super neat.//Are you proud of me?

Text.SourceString: I'm gonna ask Mom if I can get some new kites. My old ones are, um, broken.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm gonna ask Mom if I can get some new kites. My old ones are, um, broken.

Text.SourceString: Is my mom the love of your life?
Text.LocalizedString: Is my mom the love of your life?

Text.SourceString: Oh, cool. What does 'the love of your life' mean?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, cool. What does 'the love of your life' mean?

Text.SourceString: I'm telling Mom you said 'kind of.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm telling Mom you said 'kind of.

Text.SourceString: When I'm old like you, I want to find the love of my life too.
Text.LocalizedString: When I'm old like you, I want to find the love of my life too.

Special.SourceString: She's the love of my life.
Special.LocalizedString: She's the love of my life.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes school is boring.//<portrait=annoyed>You read all these hard books all the time. Blech!
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes school is boring.//<portrait=annoyed>You read all these hard books all the time. Blech!

Text.SourceString: I play at the beach with <NPCName>Oliver</> after school.//<portrait=happy>So much fun!//<portrait=normal>But then, we get hungry after a while, so we go home.
Text.LocalizedString: I play at the beach with <NPCName>Oliver</> after school.//<portrait=happy>So much fun!//<portrait=normal>But then, we get hungry after a while, so we go home.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Emma</> makes the yummiest fish tacos!//Sometimes she comes to our class and just hands them out to us for free.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Emma</> makes the yummiest fish tacos!//Sometimes she comes to our class and just hands them out to us for free.

Text.SourceString: She showed us how to make fish tacos, but I already knew how 'cause Mom taught me first.//So, didn't learn anything new there.
Text.LocalizedString: She showed us how to make fish tacos, but I already knew how 'cause Mom taught me first.//So, didn't learn anything new there.

Text.SourceString: I love cats. They're so fluffy and adorable.//<portrait=happy>Especially when they do that purr thing…
Text.LocalizedString: I love cats. They're so fluffy and adorable.//<portrait=happy>Especially when they do that purr thing…

Text.SourceString: I'm not gonna cut my hair, ever. I want it to be super long like Mom's.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not gonna cut my hair, ever. I want it to be super long like Mom's.

Text.SourceString: My mom always packs my lunch for school.//<portrait=doubt>She says lunch first, snacks second… Oh well.
Text.LocalizedString: My mom always packs my lunch for school.//<portrait=doubt>She says lunch first, snacks second… Oh well.

Text.SourceString: I like to wear my hair down. Just like my mom!//<portrait=normal>And Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> too.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to wear my hair down. Just like my mom!//<portrait=normal>And Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> too.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I get to stay up till ten.//<portrait=doubt>But not too much, 'cause Mom and Dad say I get grumpy in the morning if I stay up too late too late.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I get to stay up till ten.//<portrait=doubt>But not too much, 'cause Mom and Dad say I get grumpy in the morning if I stay up too late too late.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like visiting my uncles in their shop. It’s too hot and loud in there…//<portrait=sad>But Dad says sometimes we have to visit them to show we care.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like visiting my uncles in their shop. It’s too hot and loud in there…//<portrait=sad>But Dad says sometimes we have to visit them to show we care.

Text.SourceString: On the weekend, you can see <NPCName>Taco</> chilling at the town center.
Text.LocalizedString: On the weekend, you can see <NPCName>Taco</> chilling at the town center.

Text.SourceString: This one time, my mom made ice cream from tofu.//<portrait=sad>It was <Italic>not</> yummy.
Text.LocalizedString: This one time, my mom made ice cream from tofu.//<portrait=sad>It was <Italic>not</> yummy.

Text.SourceString: You better not let Mom make that for you!
Text.LocalizedString: You better not let Mom make that for you!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Yuri</> is my favorite doctor. She’s supercool.//<portrait=annoyed>But when I have the tiniest cold, she’s always like, “No surfing too long.” No this, no that…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Yuri</> is my favorite doctor. She’s supercool.//<portrait=annoyed>But when I have the tiniest cold, she’s always like, “No surfing too long.” No this, no that…

Text.SourceString: Mom says coffee keeps you up at night, and too much gives you a headache.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom says coffee keeps you up at night, and too much gives you a headache.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to remember birthdays, so I keep a list of my friends’ birthdays in my room.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to remember birthdays, so I keep a list of my friends’ birthdays in my room.

Text.SourceString: I have sixteen people on my list so far.
Text.LocalizedString: I have sixteen people on my list so far.

Text.SourceString: I gotta be super careful about what I take from the forest, 'cause there are mushrooms there that could make you sick.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta be super careful about what I take from the forest, 'cause there are mushrooms there that could make you sick.

Text.SourceString: I'm only allowed to go to the forest with an adult, like Aunt <NPCName>Alice</>, or when <NPCName>Archie</> asks his dad to go with us.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm only allowed to go to the forest with an adult, like Aunt <NPCName>Alice</>, or when <NPCName>Archie</> asks his dad to go with us.

Text.SourceString: My dad can only visit a couple of days a week, so he isn’t here most of the time.
Text.LocalizedString: My dad can only visit a couple of days a week, so he isn’t here most of the time.

Text.SourceString: But when it’s festival time, he takes a day off to play with me for the whole day!//<portrait=normal>Pretty cool, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: But when it’s festival time, he takes a day off to play with me for the whole day!//<portrait=normal>Pretty cool, huh?

Text.SourceString: I guess I play on the beach a lot after school because I live there. I don’t think Mom would let me go anywhere else on weekdays.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I play on the beach a lot after school because I live there. I don’t think Mom would let me go anywhere else on weekdays.

Text.SourceString: It's not really safe for me to explore when it's dark. So I gotta be home before dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: It's not really safe for me to explore when it's dark. So I gotta be home before dinner.

Text.SourceString: I'm allowed to play after school as long as I finish my reading.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm allowed to play after school as long as I finish my reading.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> doesn’t really give us homework anyway. So I usually just watch TV or play with my toys after dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> doesn’t really give us homework anyway. So I usually just watch TV or play with my toys after dinner.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie</> says he wants to be a vet and take care of sick animals when he grows up.//I think that’s a great idea.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie</> says he wants to be a vet and take care of sick animals when he grows up.//I think that’s a great idea.

Text.SourceString: I’m kinda small right now, but I’m eating my vegetables and keeping active, so I’m on my way to becoming big and strong.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m kinda small right now, but I’m eating my vegetables and keeping active, so I’m on my way to becoming big and strong.

Text.SourceString: Umm… Yup.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… Yup.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what Mom’s cooking for dinner tonight. I sure hope it isn’t edamame again.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what Mom’s cooking for dinner tonight. I sure hope it isn’t edamame again.

Text.SourceString: I wish I had a twin, just like Mom and Aunt <NPCName>Alice</>… That would be double awesome.//We could play all day and get a double amount of snacks.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I had a twin, just like Mom and Aunt <NPCName>Alice</>… That would be double awesome.//We could play all day and get a double amount of snacks.

Text.SourceString: My mom said I don’t have to bring anything yet for the Cherry Blossom Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: My mom said I don’t have to bring anything yet for the Cherry Blossom Festival.

Text.SourceString: But I kind of want to, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: But I kind of want to, you know.

Text.SourceString: My nose is itchy.
Text.LocalizedString: My nose is itchy.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Yuri</> says I’m sensitive to pollen, just like <NPCName>Charles</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Yuri</> says I’m sensitive to pollen, just like <NPCName>Charles</>.

Text.SourceString: I like to be outside with the bugs.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to be outside with the bugs.

Text.SourceString: There are more seashells at the beach in Summer, by the way…
Text.LocalizedString: There are more seashells at the beach in Summer, by the way…

Text.SourceString: Umm… Or at least, it feels like it, anyway. I seem to be collecting more lately.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… Or at least, it feels like it, anyway. I seem to be collecting more lately.

Text.SourceString: I’m cold.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m cold.

Text.SourceString: Snowman season! Yay!
Text.LocalizedString: Snowman season! Yay!

Text.SourceString: Oh, finally! I get to dress up snowmen now and not just scarecrows.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, finally! I get to dress up snowmen now and not just scarecrows.

Text.SourceString: Psst… My mom’s and Aunt <NPCName>Alice’s</> birthdays are coming up on the 27th.
Text.LocalizedString: Psst… My mom’s and Aunt <NPCName>Alice’s</> birthdays are coming up on the 27th.

Text.SourceString: They both love minced jackfruit pies, so I asked <NPCName>Archie’s</> mom to help me bake some as a surprise.
Text.LocalizedString: They both love minced jackfruit pies, so I asked <NPCName>Archie’s</> mom to help me bake some as a surprise.

Text.SourceString: I like pies too, but only the pumpkin kind…
Text.LocalizedString: I like pies too, but only the pumpkin kind…

Text.SourceString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.

Text.SourceString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.

Text.SourceString: *yawns* Aww, I wish I could stay up and watch the rain, but it makes me really sleepy…//<portrait=sad>Humph… I should probably go to bed.
Text.LocalizedString: *yawns* Aww, I wish I could stay up and watch the rain, but it makes me really sleepy…//<portrait=sad>Humph… I should probably go to bed.

Text.SourceString: Good night…
Text.LocalizedString: Good night…

Text.SourceString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.

Text.SourceString: [A sudden clap of thunder.] Aaaaa!
Text.LocalizedString: [A sudden clap of thunder.] Aaaaa!

Text.SourceString: Oh, sorry. I’m afraid of thunder. I bet you’re not afraid of anything.//I mean, you live on a farm, and you make your own food!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, sorry. I’m afraid of thunder. I bet you’re not afraid of anything.//I mean, you live on a farm, and you make your own food!

Text.SourceString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, do you know one of the many, many reasons I love rain?//<portrait=normal>Because at school, we get to stay inside and play.

Text.SourceString: Oh, sorry. I’m afraid of thunder. Gotta go.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, sorry. I’m afraid of thunder. Gotta go.

Text.SourceString: Yay! It’s snowing. I can’t wait to see how deep the snow is tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Yay! It’s snowing. I can’t wait to see how deep the snow is tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I hope there’s enough for <NPCName>Oliver</>, <NPCName>Archie</>, and me to make a snowman.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope there’s enough for <NPCName>Oliver</>, <NPCName>Archie</>, and me to make a snowman.

Text.SourceString: Yay! It’s snowing.
Text.LocalizedString: Yay! It’s snowing.

Text.SourceString: I hope it’s piling up really fast so there’s enough for <NPCName>Ollie</>, <NPCName>Archie</>, and me to make a snowman.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it’s piling up really fast so there’s enough for <NPCName>Ollie</>, <NPCName>Archie</>, and me to make a snowman.

Text.SourceString: Yay! It’s snowing.
Text.LocalizedString: Yay! It’s snowing.

Text.SourceString: I hope it’s piling up really fast so there’s enough for <NPCName>Ollie</>, <NPCName>Archie</>, and me to make a snowman.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it’s piling up really fast so there’s enough for <NPCName>Ollie</>, <NPCName>Archie</>, and me to make a snowman.

Text.SourceString: Yay! It’s snowing.
Text.LocalizedString: Yay! It’s snowing.

Text.SourceString: I need to find Mom’s extra scarf for my snowman.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to find Mom’s extra scarf for my snowman.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Where is it…
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Where is it…

Text.SourceString: I brought some lunch with me, so I don’t have to go home so soon.
Text.LocalizedString: I brought some lunch with me, so I don’t have to go home so soon.

Text.SourceString: I like to be outside with the bugs.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to be outside with the bugs.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you too?//<portrait=happy>I’m not surprised. You kinda smell like one too.//It’s a good thing! I wish I smelled like bugs.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you too?//<portrait=happy>I’m not surprised. You kinda smell like one too.//It’s a good thing! I wish I smelled like bugs.

Text.SourceString: You need to make sure the head of the snowman is a smaller ball than the body.
Text.LocalizedString: You need to make sure the head of the snowman is a smaller ball than the body.

Text.SourceString: If you have an extra Winter hat, you can put it on your snowman to make it fancy!
Text.LocalizedString: If you have an extra Winter hat, you can put it on your snowman to make it fancy!

Text.SourceString: I wanna play with the cats…//<portrait=doubt>But they don’t go out very much.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna play with the cats…//<portrait=doubt>But they don’t go out very much.

Text.SourceString: Oh, they live over there. At the house behind the welcome sign.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, they live over there. At the house behind the welcome sign.

Text.SourceString: I think if Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> had a daughter, she’d look like me… Don’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: I think if Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> had a daughter, she’d look like me… Don’t you?

Text.SourceString: I was just thinking about <NPCName>Nina</>'s fancy hats.
Text.LocalizedString: I was just thinking about <NPCName>Nina</>'s fancy hats.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, so… <NPCName>Nina</> said I could borrow her hats for dress-up.//She has so many that I can use some for my snowmen. Do you have fancy hats too?
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, so… <NPCName>Nina</> said I could borrow her hats for dress-up.//She has so many that I can use some for my snowmen. Do you have fancy hats too?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</> likes to play in the fountain.//<portrait=normal>Mom said it’s okay because he’s a dog.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> likes to play in the fountain.//<portrait=normal>Mom said it’s okay because he’s a dog.

Text.SourceString: But if he can't get out, I gotta get a grown-up to help.
Text.LocalizedString: But if he can't get out, I gotta get a grown-up to help.

Text.SourceString: Mom doesn't like it when I use her stuff to dress up the scarecrows.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom doesn't like it when I use her stuff to dress up the scarecrows.

Text.SourceString: My clothes are too small, so I gotta use hers.
Text.LocalizedString: My clothes are too small, so I gotta use hers.

Text.SourceString: I don’t really play with <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>. They don’t go out very much.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really play with <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>. They don’t go out very much.

Text.SourceString: Also, they always run away every time I try to pet them.
Text.LocalizedString: Also, they always run away every time I try to pet them.

Text.SourceString: If you have good farmer jokes, let me know. I might put them in my book.
Text.LocalizedString: If you have good farmer jokes, let me know. I might put them in my book.

Text.SourceString: If I publish it and we’re famous, we can make another one so we get even more famous!
Text.LocalizedString: If I publish it and we’re famous, we can make another one so we get even more famous!

Text.SourceString: How many scarecrows do we have on our farm? Can I keep one in my room?
Text.LocalizedString: How many scarecrows do we have on our farm? Can I keep one in my room?

Text.SourceString: I’m not good at mini golf yet, but Dad says I have a strong swing.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not good at mini golf yet, but Dad says I have a strong swing.

Text.SourceString: One day, when I'm all grown up, I wanna buy my own island.//Me, Mom, and all my pets will live there!
Text.LocalizedString: One day, when I'm all grown up, I wanna buy my own island.//Me, Mom, and all my pets will live there!

Text.SourceString: You can come too, but then who's gonna run the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: You can come too, but then who's gonna run the farm?

Text.SourceString: I’m going to write the prettiest poem in the world and send it to Nana.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to write the prettiest poem in the world and send it to Nana.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to paint the prettiest painting in the world. It’ll have birds, and all kinds of flowers, and robot scarecrows.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to paint the prettiest painting in the world. It’ll have birds, and all kinds of flowers, and robot scarecrows.

Text.SourceString: Maybe not today… I’m having too much fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe not today… I’m having too much fun.

Text.SourceString: I still don’t know what I wanna be when I grow up.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll be a blacksmith like Nana and Papa!
Text.LocalizedString: I still don’t know what I wanna be when I grow up.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll be a blacksmith like Nana and Papa!

Text.SourceString: Green smoothies are okay.//<portrait=annoyed>They don’t taste terrible, but I wish Mom would just stop making them.
Text.LocalizedString: Green smoothies are okay.//<portrait=annoyed>They don’t taste terrible, but I wish Mom would just stop making them.

Text.SourceString: Yuck…
Text.LocalizedString: Yuck…

Text.SourceString: Mom says a wool hat isn’t for snowmen.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom says a wool hat isn’t for snowmen.

Text.SourceString: Can I borrow your hats for my snowmen, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I borrow your hats for my snowmen, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>?

Text.SourceString: I don’t feel like playing mini golf today.//So I think I’ll just play around here.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t feel like playing mini golf today.//So I think I’ll just play around here.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Oliver</> always has cookies in his pocket, and he always shares with us.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Oliver</> always has cookies in his pocket, and he always shares with us.

Text.SourceString: I never ever want to leave. I want to live with Mom forever and ever!
Text.LocalizedString: I never ever want to leave. I want to live with Mom forever and ever!

Text.SourceString: Eggplant lasagna is okay.//<portrait=annoyed>It's...alright, I guess. It doesn't taste terrible, but I wish Mom would stop making it. Yuck!
Text.LocalizedString: Eggplant lasagna is okay.//<portrait=annoyed>It's...alright, I guess. It doesn't taste terrible, but I wish Mom would stop making it. Yuck!

Text.SourceString: Yay, snow!
Text.LocalizedString: Yay, snow!

Text.SourceString: See ya later, alligator!
Text.LocalizedString: See ya later, alligator!

Text.SourceString: Do you know where to get a mistletoe?//I want to bring it when I visit Nana and Papa.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know where to get a mistletoe?//I want to bring it when I visit Nana and Papa.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna make them kiss.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna make them kiss.

Text.SourceString: I don't like going to my uncle's house in the Summer.//It's super-duper hot there.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't like going to my uncle's house in the Summer.//It's super-duper hot there.

Text.SourceString: I like going to Dad’s house. Nana and Papa live right next door, and I get to see them all the time!//<portrait=happy>Plus, in the Summer, Nana always has lots of starfruits growing in her garden.

Text.SourceString: Some of my clothes are still at Dad’s house.//I keep my fairy dress there because Nana and I put on fairy dresses in Spring and bless the garden before we start planting for the year.//<portrait=happy>Nana is cool!
